# Tariff Scraping System

## Project Structure

```
project/
+-- monitor.py                   # Change detection + scrape dispatch
+-- run_scraper.py               # CLI entry point
+-- scrapers/
|   +-- __init__.py
|   +-- base.py                  # BaseTariffScraper + schema + clean_numeric()
|   +-- registry.py              # Supplier registry
|   +-- electric_ireland.py      # Electric Ireland scraper
|   +-- template_supplier.py     # Copy for new suppliers
+-- data/tariffs/
    +-- .page_hashes.json        # Persisted hashes (auto-created)
    +-- clean/
        +-- electric_ireland_auto.csv
```

## Output Schema (matches matching.py)

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| supplier | str | e.g. "Electric Ireland" |
| plan_name | str | Plan display name |
| meter_type | str | "24h" / "daynight" / "smart" |
| unit_rate_day_eur_kwh | float | Day/standard rate |
| unit_rate_night_eur_kwh | float | Night rate (NaN if N/A) |
| unit_rate_peak_eur_kwh | float | Peak rate (NaN if N/A) |
| unit_rate_24h_eur_kwh | float | Flat 24h rate (NaN if not flat) |
| standing_charge_eur_year | float | Annual standing charge |
| discount_percent | float | Headline discount (0.0 if none) |
| structure | str | "24h" / "DayNight" / "3-Period" |
| scraped_at | str | ISO-8601 UTC timestamp |

## Usage

```bash
# One-shot with change detection
python run_scraper.py electric_ireland

# Force re-scrape
python run_scraper.py electric_ireland --force

# All suppliers
python run_scraper.py --all

# Continuous monitoring
python monitor.py --interval 3600
```

## Adding a New Supplier

1. Copy template_supplier.py to e.g. scrapers/sse_airtricity.py
2. Set supplier_name and target_url
3. Implement scrape() with appropriate selectors
4. Register in scrapers/registry.py

## Dependencies

```
playwright
pandas
```

Install browsers: `playwright install chromium`